### Sample HTTP requests for TranslateHub API

### Project Management

# 1. Create a new project
POST http://localhost:8080/projects
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Japanese Translation Project",
    "source_lang": "en",
    "target_lang": "jp"
}

# 2. List all projects
GET http://localhost:8080/projects

# 3. Get a specific project
GET http://localhost:8080/projects/1

### Task Management

# 4. Create a translation task for a specific project
POST http://localhost:8080/projects/1/tasks
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="dialogue.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Hello, how are you?
This is a test.
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="name"

Chapter 1 Translation
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="creator"

alice
--boundary--

# 5. List tasks for a specific project
GET http://localhost:8080/projects/1/tasks

# 6. List all tasks (across all projects)
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks

# 7. Get a specific task with its dialogues
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/1

### Translation Changes

# 8. Submit a translation change for a dialogue line
POST http://localhost:8080/changes
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

task_id=1&dialogue_id=1&user=bob&new_trans=こんにちは、お元気ですか？

# 9. Review (approve) a submitted change
POST http://localhost:8080/review
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

task_id=1&change_id=1&user=alice&status=approved

# 10. Review (reject) a submitted change
POST http://localhost:8080/review
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

task_id=1&change_id=1&user=alice&status=rejected
